
[1]creed

   CREED, n. [This word seems to have been introduced by the use of the
   Latin credo, I believe, at the beginning of the Apostles creed, or
   brief system of Christian faith. See Creed.]

   1. A brief summary of the articles of Christian faith; a symbol; as the
   Apostolic creed.

   2. That which is believed; any system of principles which are believed
   or professed; as a political creed.
